<edge source="Noah Carter" target="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d7">28.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The World Athletics Federation is responsible for overseeing the rules, regulations, and validation of athletic performances, including those of athlete Noah Carter. This federation ensures compliance with international standards in championship events and other competitions where Noah Carter participates. Specifically, it validates records set by athletes such as his new 100m sprint record achieved using carbon-fiber spikes. The World Athletics Federation's oversight extends beyond individual achievements to encompass the broader context of championships, ensuring that all rules are adhered to and verifying any record-breaking performances. This includes validating specific achievements like Noah Carter’s sprint record as well as general compliance with regulations for competitions in which he participates. The federation is tasked with overseeing record validations and equipment use by athletes participating in major championship events.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation validates and records new athletic achievements like the one set by Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of records set at competitions like those where Noah Carter competes.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the rules and records for athletes competing in championships.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the rules and regulations for athletes like Noah Carter participating in international competitions.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of records and regulations for athletes like Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the rules and regulations that Noah Carter must adhere to during competitions.</data>
  <data key="d9">athlete achievement,athlete compliance,athlete management,athlete oversight,athlete recognition,athlete regulation,athlete supervision,athletic achievement,competition oversight,governance,record validation,regulation,validation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d02e98febcd8f8650bbe77d789a41d69&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-490df5a6810de4f040c4fe2681e6ed6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0944d4a59fb7a84bd79d2fca8361e518&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-25d7c29d65aa0e4d54fb4af54207fa0d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-333af5cc1ff286e512f36be66d1aa78b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0d3b88d3601a1081c8354e0ef27952f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95280ea367581dac710f0dc56c7a72f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72f381579d364fa91cc3e73153e0af97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1e7cec156f57837e8d25cbe83a6db45f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41be59e9bae9e87a716afd8b5a9e9ee1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-068ca517cbebf973fd4089bd45ef615c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2a0171ee9d19cc664d4d041d3e73ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9e37e8f7e8a98183b1724c16ce814a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-942b136689124792272bc32a2898842c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf168eec40aae386455af5027929f6fe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-39206ec5906f23d68e051b1df74d3ca7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c1fca5402ff2eb1c53222e1d4db282a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfcf7e8f6051fb59b7f2cec85fa4dc4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-203eba714089c79438cfc39755f054ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-56b76e765b58a558604d5d6f2575d2ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a83bcdf6e7b7269cfd17b4f21457de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a81645d1d338ac013fa594b14c35640&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d3d3acb3c191c9e65fac21b5ed9284f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-412e17859c430b9ce8b929bc152053ef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3781d1671ca7126e99e7656264965fb6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5479196dee25b34d077c01190c6c728b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c4967b23b72f04d5c4ef37149d21ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0640212d45b4b92d91d0255cf90edf96</data>
