<edge source="Market Selloff" target="Nexon Technologies">
  <data key="d7">9.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Market Selloff, as it pertains to Nexon Technologies, refers to a significant decline in the company's stock price that is influenced by broader market conditions. The primary factors contributing to this market selloff include rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty. These external economic pressures have led to increased investor concerns over earnings forecasts and compliance issues for Nexon Technologies.

The decline in Nexon Technologies' stock has not only reflected these broader market trends but also contributed to the overall market selloff, affecting indices such as the Global Tech Index. This phenomenon underscores the interconnectedness of individual company performances with macroeconomic indicators and regulatory environments.&lt;SEP&gt;Nexon Technologies' stock decline contributed to the broader market selloff driven by investor concerns.</data>
